item.title: CVE-2018-0507|2024-08-05T03:28:10.680Z -- nippon%20telegraph%20and%20telephone%20east%20corporation -- flet%27s%20virus%20clear%20easy%20setup%20%26%20application%20tool
item.description: Untrusted search path vulnerability in FLET'S VIRUS CLEAR Easy Setup & Application Tool ver.11 and earlier versions, FLET'S VIRUS CLEAR v6 Easy Setup & Application Tool ver.11 and earlier versions allow an attacker to gain privileges via a Trojan horse DLL in an unspecified directory.

item.title: CVE-2017-10829|2024-08-05T17:50:12.039Z -- nippon%20telegraph%20and%20telephone%20east%20corporation -- remote%20support%20tool%20%28enkaku%20support%20tool%29
item.description: Untrusted search path vulnerability in Remote Support Tool (Enkaku Support Tool) All versions distributed through the website till 2017 August 10 allow an attacker to gain privileges via a Trojan horse DLL in an unspecified directory.

item.title: CVE-2018-0665|2024-08-05T03:35:49.253Z -- nippon%20telegraph%20and%20telephone%20east%20corporation -- biz%20box%20router%20n58i%2C%20and%20n500
item.description: Yamaha routers RT57i Rev.8.00.95 and earlier, RT58i Rev.9.01.51 and earlier, NVR500 Rev.11.00.36 and earlier, RTX810 Rev.11.01.31 and earlier, allow an administrative user to embed arbitrary scripts to the configuration data through a certain form field of the configuration page, which may be executed on another administrative user's web browser. This is a different vulnerability from CVE-2018-0666.

Untrusted search path vulnerability in the installer of FLET'S VIRUS CLEAR Easy Setup & Application Tool ver.13.0 and earlier versions and FLET'S VIRUS CLEAR v6 Easy Setup & Application Tool ver.13.0 and earlier versions allows an attacker to gain privileges via a Trojan horse DLL in an unspecified directory.

item.title: CVE-2017-10874|2024-08-05T17:50:12.521Z -- nippon%20telegraph%20and%20telephone%20east%20corporation -- pwr-q200
item.description: PWR-Q200 does not use random values for source ports of DNS query packets, which allows remote attackers to conduct DNS cache poisoning attacks.

This is a different vulnerability from CVE-2018-0665.
